Run the model on a NeuronCore through the AWS Neuron SDK's PyTorch support, in an efficient dtype (`torch.bfloat16`). Do NOT run inference on CPU or in `float32` — it will be far too slow. NeuronCores execute compiled graphs, so make sure the hot path actually compiles and runs on the device rather than staying on CPU. The first compile of each new graph shape takes minutes — reuse the persistent compile cache and keep shapes static so later steps hit the cache instead of recompiling. Use whichever Neuron PyTorch approach is current for inference (check the Neuron skills/docs); don't assume a specific API.
